= Abstract
This project utilizes the chest X-ray anomaly detection dataset released by VinBigData for the 2021 Kaggle competition, with the objective of developing a high-performing detection model for the challenging task of chest anomaly detection. This domain is particularly demanding, as even subtle abnormalities can have significant clinical consequences.

The final metrics of our ensemble approach combine YOLO and Faster R-CNN using advanced Weighted Box Fusion (WBF), significantly pushing detection performance metrics implicitly beyond single standalone frameworks. This report documents the extensive inputs, baseline tests, ensemble optimizations, and mathematical logic generated to achieve robust mapping convergence natively onto 14 abnormality classes.
